name: 2025 DGPT+ The Open at Austin - Harvey Penick FPO

liveLayoutDetails.notes: OB: All area outside of marked island green and tee area. DROP ZONE: After any throw from the tee area coming to rest OB, player must proceed to DZ+1 penalty throw. Standard OB rules apply on all subsequent throws.

OB: Marked lines right and left of the fairway, surrounding the green and beyond; Traditional golf green. HAZARD: Traditional golf bunkers. DROP ZONE: After any throw from the tee area coming to rest OB in the creek bed or right side of the fairway, player must proceed to DZ +1 penalty throw. Standard OB rules apply for all OB tee shots left of the fairway and any subsequent throws. NOTE: Do not attempt to retrieve discs coming to rest in the creekbed.
OB: Marked line left/long and beyond; Traditional golf green.
OB: Marked line left, right, long and beyond; Traditional golf green.

OB: Marked line running in front of the MPO tee area, defining the left edge fairway, connecting left to the dirt cart path surrounding the green and beyond. 

DROP ZONE: After any throw coming to rest OB, player may proceed to DZ +1 penalty throw. Standard OB rules apply.

OB: Marked line along edge of creek right/long and beyond. MANDATORIES: Discs must not enter restricted planes right of either marked tree. If either MANDO is missed, proceed to corresponding DZ +1 penalty throw.
OB: Marked line along edge of creek left and beyond.
OB: Marked line along edge of creek left and beyond.
OB: All area outside of marked safe fairway/green, including traditional golf green.
OB: All area outside of marked ISLAND GREEN.
OB: Marked lines left and right of fairway and beyond, including traditional golf green short of the basket. OB lines extend to infinity. HAZARD: Traditional golf bunker.
OB: Marked line right and beyond. OB line extends to infinity. MANDATORY: Discs must not enter restricted plane right of marked tree. If MANDO is missed, re-tee +1 penalty throw.

OB: Marked creek area dividing fairway; Marked line long and beyond. Marked line left and beyond. DROP ZONE: After any throw coming to rest in the OB Creek area, or left of fairway before creek gap, player may proceed to DZ +1 penalty throw. Standard OB rules apply. MPO DZ is the FPO tee. FPO DZ is forward near fence in front of the creek.
OB: Marked line left and beyond until the end of the wooded section of the hole; Marked line right and beyond including traditional golf green. HAZARD: Traditional golf bunker near MPO basket.
OB: Marked line left/long and beyond; Traditional golf green. OB lines extend to infinity. NOTE: Bench in fairway is casual area.
OB: Marked line left, long and beyond; On or beyond concrete bike right trail. HAZARD: All traditional golf bunkers near basket.
OB: Marked line left and beyond. MANDATORY: Discs must not enter restricted plane right of marked tree. If MANDO is missed, proceed to DZ +1 penalty throw.

OB: Marked lines left and right of fairway and beyond. MANDATORIES: Discs must not enter restricted planes right of either marked tree. If either MANDO is missed, proceed to corresponding DZ +1 penalty throw. (DZ for first MANDO is the FPO tee.)

OB: All area surrounding marked ISLAND GREEN.DROP ZONE: After any throw from the tee area coming to rest OB, player MUST proceed to DZ +1 penalty throw.  Standard OB rules apply on all subsequent throws.

OB: Marked lines left, right, and long of fairway and beyond.DROP ZONE: After any throw from the tee area that never crosses in-bounds, player MUST proceed to DZ1 (short tee) +1 penalty throw. After any throw from the fairway that crosses the in-bounds ISLAND GREEN and comes to rest OB, player MUST proceed to DZ2 +1 penalty throw.  Standard OB rules apply on all other throws.	After four consecutive throws from the fairway that finish OB without crossing the island green, a player may advance to DZ2+1 penalty instead of continuing to throw from the last 	point in boundsCERTIFIED OFFICIAL - will make the call - OB Island - There will be unified signal to identify need to go to drop zone. Spotter will point to player if never crossed the island.
